Early Medieval Art
Praeger Publishers | 1969 | ISBN: N/A | English | 276 pages | PDF | 56.8 MB

When Charlemagne was crowned Emperor of the West in ad 800, political coherence was re-established in Western Europe, and with it began a concurrent artistic reawakening we now call the Carolingian renovatio. John Beckwith traces here the fascinating story of medieval art as it evolved from this early revival of imperial tradition to the full glory of Romanesque achievement
